This is the python implemntation of a supervised classification algorithm that predicts the gender of names. The ML algorithm used is Decision Tree Classifier.

It provides a 98% of training accuracy and a 86% of testing accuracy when evaluated with the dataset dataset/dataset.csv and a 0.3 testing size / 0.7 training size. 

Syntax:

python NameGender.py accuracy [path_to_dataset.csv] [test_size] 
python NameGender.py predict [path_to_dataset.csv] [test_size] [names_to_predict.txt]

Examples:


INPUT
    python NameGender.py accuracy dataset/dataset.csv 0.3

OUTPUT
    Accuracy on Training Set: 0.988845
    Accuracy on Testing Set: 0.864634

INPUT
    python NameGender.py predict dataset/dataset.csv 0.3 names.txt
OUTPUT
            Name       Gender
     Rodrigo            M
        Sara            F
        Sera            F
        Ruth            F
     Phoenix            M
     Joaquin            M
